HEADWORD: Brokerage
<hw>Bro"ker*age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
business or employment of a broker.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fee, reward, or commission, given or changed for
transacting business as a broker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>broker-dealer</ent>⟦br⟧
